    "body":  "# The Civic Desk v0.3.2 public beta\n\nWindows-only public beta for CivicNewspaper / The Civic Desk.\n\n## Download\n\n- Installer: `The.Civic.Desk_0.3.2_x64-setup.exe`\n- SHA256: `8204BB4210DD284518D114C57A3089BAC11D7B0EC8E0F83D8D61928D44FEB6E0`\n- Size: `5240548` bytes\n- Checksum file: `SHA256SUMS.txt`\n\n## Current candidate\n\n- Product build commit: `35e6cf0f4a8f01d74ef79247feaaadbd34dbb3da`\n- Docs/evidence commit: `62a44b1ea4b4ea3ba05a76811d9c45af37d825c8`\n- Status: awaiting final cleanroom tester recheck for this rebuilt artifact.\n\nThis rebuild includes the prior v0.3.2 repairs plus onboarding identity reconciliation before Daily Scan, stricter downgrading for unsupported/model-suggested Daily Scan leads, full state-name normalization during source discovery, weak scan lead draft gating, source-quality cleanup for page/index debris, official-record Brief promotion only when linked evidence has concrete civic action, reader-facing brief format fallback, source-backed Daily Scan Brief promotion for clean official civic-service/program signals, and retained dark-signal evidence links for draftable Daily Scan briefs.\n\n## Unsigned beta installer\n\nThis installer is unsigned because this is a free public beta. Windows SmartScreen may show a warning. Verify the SHA256 above against your download. If it matches, choose **More info**, then **Run anyway**.\n\n## Scope\n\n- Supported public-beta installer: Windows `.exe` only.\n- macOS and Linux installers are backlog/proof-needed and are not release-supported for v0.3.2.\n- Default live publishing proof path: anonymous here.now preview.\n- Credentialed external providers still need user-owned credentials and provider-specific proof."
